{"questionId":"25371115","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Hyungmin designs a concrete bird bath. The bird bath is supported by a pedestal.&nbsp;This is shown in the diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/bc13628c1397132ab3ab1db3c55ab31b002a67e1.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The interior of the bird bath is in the shape of a cone with radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>, height <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> and a constant&nbsp;slant height of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi></math> be the volume of the bird bath.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Hyungmin wants the bird bath to have maximum volume.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the maximum volume of the bird bath.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2500</mn><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8675</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8675</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math><strong>&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>828</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8675</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for substituting their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>28</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8675</mn><mo>…</mo></math> in the volume formula.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>50400</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><msup><mtext>cm</mtext><mn>3</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>50383</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em>(ft)<em>(G2)</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through from part (d).</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25371115","referenceCode":"20N.2.SL.TZ0.T_4e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the maximum volume of the bird bath.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}